@startuml rabbitmq-workflow
!theme vibrant

title RabbitMQ Message Flow - Asynchronous Processing

skinparam {
  backgroundColor #FFFFFF
  componentStyle rectangle
}

actor User
participant "Frontend" as Frontend
participant "Wardrobe\nService" as Wardrobe
queue "RabbitMQ\nExchange\n(closetx_events)" as Exchange
queue "image_processing\n_queue" as ImageQueue
queue "outfit_generation\n_queue" as OutfitQueue
queue "fashion_advice\n_queue" as AdviceQueue
participant "Image\nProcessor\nWorker" as ImageWorker
participant "Outfit\nGenerator\nWorker" as OutfitWorker
participant "Fashion\nAdvice\nWorker" as FashionWorker
database "MongoDB" as DB

== Upload Photo - Image Processing Flow ==

User -> Frontend: Upload clothing photo
activate Frontend

Frontend -> Wardrobe: POST /api/wardrobe/clothing\n(multipart/form-data)
activate Wardrobe

Wardrobe -> DB: Store image in GridFS
activate DB
DB --> Wardrobe: Image ID
deactivate DB

Wardrobe -> Exchange: **PUBLISH MESSAGE**\nRouting Key: "image.analyze"\n{\n  itemId: "...",\n  imageId: "...",\n  userId: "..."\n}

Exchange -> ImageQueue: Route to queue

Wardrobe --> Frontend: 201 Created\n(item created, processing...)
deactivate Wardrobe

Frontend --> User: Show item\n"AI analyzing..."
deactivate Frontend

ImageQueue -> ImageWorker: **CONSUME MESSAGE**
activate ImageWorker

ImageWorker -> DB: Fetch image from GridFS
activate DB
DB --> ImageWorker: Image data
deactivate DB

ImageWorker -> ImageWorker: Call Google Vision AI\nAnalyze image

ImageWorker -> DB: Update item with AI results
activate DB
DB --> ImageWorker: Updated
deactivate DB

ImageWorker -> ImageQueue: **ACK** (acknowledge)
deactivate ImageWorker

note right of ImageQueue
  **Message Properties:**
  - Durable: true
  - Persistent: true
  - Manual ACK: true
  
  **Ensures:**
  - Messages survive restarts
  - No message loss
  - Retry on failure
end note

== Outfit Generation Flow ==

User -> Frontend: Request outfit
activate Frontend

Frontend -> Wardrobe: GET /api/outfits/daily
activate Wardrobe

Wardrobe -> Exchange: **PUBLISH MESSAGE**\nRouting Key: "outfit.generate"

Exchange -> OutfitQueue: Route to queue

Wardrobe --> Frontend: 202 Accepted\n(processing...)
deactivate Wardrobe

Frontend --> User: "Generating outfits..."
deactivate Frontend

OutfitQueue -> OutfitWorker: **CONSUME MESSAGE**
activate OutfitWorker

OutfitWorker -> DB: Fetch wardrobe items
OutfitWorker -> OutfitWorker: Run algorithms\n- Color harmony\n- Style matching\n- Weather scoring

OutfitWorker -> DB: Save generated outfits
OutfitWorker -> OutfitQueue: **ACK**
deactivate OutfitWorker

== Fashion Advice Flow ==

User -> Frontend: Ask for styling tips
activate Frontend

Frontend -> Wardrobe: POST /api/outfits/ai-advice
activate Wardrobe

Wardrobe -> Exchange: **PUBLISH MESSAGE**\nRouting Key: "fashion.advice"

Exchange -> AdviceQueue: Route to queue

Wardrobe --> Frontend: 202 Accepted
deactivate Wardrobe

Frontend --> User: "Getting advice..."
deactivate Frontend

AdviceQueue -> FashionWorker: **CONSUME MESSAGE**
activate FashionWorker

FashionWorker -> FashionWorker: Call Ollama LLM\nGenerate advice

FashionWorker -> DB: Store advice
FashionWorker -> AdviceQueue: **ACK**
deactivate FashionWorker

note right of Queue
  **Exchange Type:** Topic
  
  **Routing Keys:**
  - image.analyze → image_processing_queue
  - outfit.generate → outfit_generation_queue
  - fashion.advice → fashion_advice_queue
  
  **Benefits:**
  - Flexible routing
  - Multiple consumers per queue
  - Decoupled services
end note

@enduml
